1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,960
One little cream, born on a Friday, rough and nameless,

2
00:00:04,480 --> 00:00:09,260
sold, made proper, restocked, watched from the road,

3
00:00:09,580 --> 00:00:10,720
counted to the franc.

4
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:16,000
Banco measured all of it, but there's one thing.

5
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:18,020
The numbers still can't tell us.

6
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:20,220
Did it actually work?

7
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,600
Was it worth 40 francs?

8
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:26,300
Only the people who took it home can answer that.

9
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:28,820
Larry, Sally, the next nervous customer,

10
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:29,820
holding the tube.

11
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:34,060
So in season two, we hand them the pen.

12
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:36,280
Here's how it's going to work.

13
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:38,660
They never give us an email.

14
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:41,980
They never do. A first name, maybe an Instagram.

15
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:44,560
That's enough, because on the receipt

16
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:47,180
is a little QR code.

17
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:50,540
They scan it, no app, no password,

18
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:52,500
and up comes one quick question.

19
00:00:52,860 --> 00:00:53,820
Did it work?

20
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:57,400
10 seconds, a thumbs-up, a star.

21
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:58,520
Would you buy it again?

22
00:00:58,520 --> 00:01:03,040
Maybe a photo, a 10-second clip of a calming the bite.

23
00:01:03,460 --> 00:01:07,000
And for their honesty, they are in points, real credit,

24
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,260
toward their next visit.

25
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:13,340
Those words don't vanish into a database.

26
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,960
They land on the cream itself.

27
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:19,920
So the next person who hesitates doesn't just see a price.

28
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:21,700
They see Larry.

29
00:01:21,980 --> 00:01:22,720
They see Sally.

30
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:24,640
They see it work.

31
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:27,980
The cream stops selling on Felix's word

32
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:30,940
and starts selling on the neighborhoods.

33
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,020
And Felix from the road finally sees the whole picture,

34
00:01:35,740 --> 00:01:39,040
not just what sold, but what helped, the velocity,

35
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,780
and the reason behind it.

36
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:45,000
That's the loop born once, then known,

37
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:47,780
by the people who carried it home.

38
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:51,360
We're building it right now, season two of Banco,

39
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:55,420
where the shop stops talking in the neighborhood starts.

40
00:01:56,260 --> 00:01:58,340
Born once, known forever.
